{"data": {"blog": {"university-of-cambridge-2474": {"": "#### \\\\u{1f393} Near Social Profile: @c7231475ec87b9fef12f5a5ea34a282447bab4d1be4eadc4a23e7bbb1533c11c\\\\n.\\\\n.\\\\n#### \\\\u{1f393} Website: https://cambridgeblockchain.org/\\\\n.\\\\n.\\\\n#### \\\\u{1f393} About\\\\n\\\\nStudent-run society at the University of Cambridge, and we are scaling the Blockchain space at Cambridge and beyond.\\\\nFounded by students in 2018, our mission is to foster a booming Blockchain ecosystem at Cambridge by maintaining a distributed network of students, researchers, entrepreneurs, investors and industry partners.\\\\n\\\\nProposal Near Social: https://near.social/devgovgigs.near/widget/gigs-board.pages.Post?id=2160\\\\n\\\\n#### \\\\u{1f393} What they do\\\\n\\\\n**Education**\\\\n\\\\nTeaching open-source courses\\\\n\\\\nWorkshops and hackathons held by experts\\\\n\\\\n**Academic Research**\\\\n\\\\nFuelling new academic research at Cambridge Translating developments into use cases.\\\\n\\\\n**Advisory**\\\\n\\\\nOur team of highly dedicated academics and researchers advise companies and groups on the Legal, Technical and Business aspects of Blockchain.\\\\n\\\\n**Entrepreneurship**\\\\n\\\\nWe incentivise innovation through large prizes in competitions. {"data": {"blog": {"arizona-state-university-2478": {"": "#### Near Social Profile: @blockchainatasu.near\\\\n.\\\\n.\\\\n#### Website: https://blockchainucsb.com/\\\\n.\\\\n.\\\\n#### \\\\u{1f393} About \\\\n\\\\nWe are Arizona State University students, faculty, and staff who believe in the positive impact blockchain technology can have on the world around us. We are developers building solutions, scholars performing research, and innovators working to change the world.\\\\n\\\\n[Click here to learn more about our leadership team.](https://blockchain.asu.edu/team/)\\\\n\\\\nProposal Near Social: https://near.social/devgovgigs.near/widget/gigs-board.pages.Post?id=1691\\\\n\\\\n#### \\\\u{1f393} What they do\\\\n\\\\nThe ASU Blockchain Research Lab\\\\u{2019}s mission is to\\\\u{a0}advance the research and development of blockchain-based technologies for use in Business, Finance, Economics, Mathematics, Computer Science, and all other areas of potential impact.\\\\n\\\\nSince the Lab\\\\u{2019}s creation in early 2017, we have partnered with dozens of industry leaders to provide blockchain backed solutions for real-world problems. {"data": {"blog": {"university-of-illinois-at-urbana-champaign-2479": {"": "#### \\\\u{1f393} Near Social Profile: @2e64e275dfaf612d6790d7fcb11450edd8bdd357bec7324a4c5290878cfae37d\\\\n.\\\\n.\\\\n#### \\\\u{1f393} Website: https://illiniblockchain.com/\\\\n.\\\\n.\\\\n#### \\\\u{1f393} Overview\\\\n\\\\nEstablished in 2021, Illini Blockchain is a curiosity-driven club whose mission is to learn about and contribute to the blockchain ecosystem.\\\\n\\\\nIllini Blockchain was started on the belief that the new applications enabled by blockchain technologies will have an impact on the future, and sought that the talented students, alumni, and faculty have the ability to be at the forefront of the industry.\\\\n\\\\nWe want to foster the blockchain ecosystem on campus for everyone interested, helping people learn the technology and applications, building projects, and engaging in research.\\\\n\\\\nProposal Near Social: https://near.social/devgovgigs.near/widget/gigs-board.pages.Post?id=1573", "metadata": {"id": 2479, "title": "University of Illinois at Urbana Champaign", "author": "8566fc4bb16e1a7446b5e9b1b8aea94b5751d5f8c658d7af18d8cdf642d7b31d", "status": "DRAFT", "category": "guide", "subtitle": "Illini Blockchain Club", "createdAt": "2023-12-13", "updatedAt": "2023-12-13", "description": "Illini Blockchain Club", "publishedAt": "2023-12-13", "communityAddonId": "blogv2"}}}}, "handle": "near-campus"}

{"data": {"blog": {"university-of-california,-san-diego-2507": {"": "#### \\\\u{1f393} Near Social Profile: @2d43bcf331706f4a8378c16f1691c95216459da22ca568a29ffb5f285a6503e4\\\\n.\\\\n.\\\\n#### \\\\u{1f393} Website: https://blockchain.ucsd.edu/\\\\n.\\\\n.\\\\n#### \\\\u{1f393} Overview\\\\n\\\\nBlockchain at San Diego is team of students at UCSD focused on advancing innovation on the blockchain through education, research, and development.\\\\n\\\\nWe strive to equip students with foundational knowledge and resources to successfully navigate the fast-evolving blockchain space and help us engineer novel blockchain solutions.\\\\n\\\\nWe partner with prominent individuals, organizations, and companies in the industry to provide practical education and connect our members to exciting career opportunities.\\\\n\\\\nProposal Near Social: https://near.social/devgovgigs.near/widget/gigs-board.pages.Post?id=1918", "metadata": {"id": 2507, "title": "University of California, San Diego", "author": "8566fc4bb16e1a7446b5e9b1b8aea94b5751d5f8c658d7af18d8cdf642d7b31d", "status": "DRAFT", "category": "guide", "subtitle": "Blockchain At UC San Diego", "createdAt": "2023-12-13", "updatedAt": "2023-12-13", "description": "Blockchain At UC San Diego", "publishedAt": "2023-12-13", "communityAddonId": "blogv2"}}}}, "handle": "near-campus"}

{"data": {"blog": {"community-call-#8-recap-2656": {"": "**MODERATORS**: Owen Hassall\\\\n**VIDEO**: https://youtu.be/Dn-HkMXAz20\\\\n\\\\n## AGENDA\\\\n- Electron Labs integration with NEAR DA\\\\n- Reclaim Protocol proposal\\\\n- ZKWASM\\\\n\\\\n## TOPIC SUMMARIES\\\\n- **Electron Labs integration with NEAR DA**: The ZK Light Client, built by Electron Labs, has completed their integration with NEAR DA. \\\\nFind out more [here](https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/18Ik_nO-7J0PZX_i69Y9oejoLWeQ1KHCePtfXFM01JIQ/edit?usp=sharing).\\\\n\\\\n- **Reclaim Protocol proposal**: There was an interesting discussion of Reclaim protocol\\\\u{2019}s proposal to DevHub that allows users to generate verifiable credentials using ZKP. Feel free to give your thoughts on the [proposal](https://near.social/devhub.near/widget/app?page=post&id=1969). You can also find out more [here](https://acrobat.adobe.com/id/urn:aaid:sc:EU:2a8bf47e-bfe4-4b95-b263-6fd07730fb58).\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n- **ZKWASM presentation by Pagoda**: We had the ZKWASM Pagoda team join us to give more information on ZKWASM, share future plans and take questions. The slides can be found [here](https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1y9mcUd8dtYMotHcXXCBqvSYwG6JaXn4gM8WMrW7Kspc/edit?usp=sharing).\\\\n\\\\n- **Other Discussion**: We also heard updates from Opact (private transactions on NEAR) introducing open-source ZK ceremonies, an update about Zpoken\\\\u{2019}s ZK light client and a quick discussion on NDC and private voting.\\\\n\\\\n## ACTION ITEMS\\\\n- Please give your thoughts and attestations on the proposal by Reclaim Protocol [here](https://near.social/devhub.near/widget/app?page=post&id=1969).", "metadata": {"id": 2656, "title": "Community Call #8 Recap", "author": "pivortex.near", "status": "DRAFT", "category": "news", "subtitle": "Electron Labs, Reclaim Protocol, ZKWASM, Opact, Zpoken, NDC Private Voting.", "createdAt": "2024-04-10", "updatedAt": "2024-04-10", "description": "Electron Labs, Reclaim Protocol, ZKWASM, Opact, Zpoken, NDC Private Voting.", "publishedAt": "2024-04-10", "communityAddonId": "blogv2"}}}}, "handle": "zero-knowledge"}
